      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help writing a rejection email. We had a candidate, Marcus, who made it all the way to the final interview for our Senior Dev role here in Austin. He's really talented and had great technical skills, but we decided to go with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud architecture. I want the email to be professional and kind because he was a great guy, but we need to be firm that the decision is final. Can you draft something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is a draft for your rejection email to Marcus. It should sound professional, while still acknowledging his impressive skills. You can tailor the tone as needed, but this hits the key points.\n\n***\n\n**Subject: Update on the Senior Developer Role at [Your Company Name]**\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview with us for the Senior Developer position. We truly enjoyed getting to know you and were very impressed with your technical abilities during the final round. The hiring committee was very impressed with your skills; however, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose background aligned slightly closer with our immediate needs regarding our specific cloud architecture.\n\nThis was a very difficult decision, as you are a highly talented individual. We genuinely appreciate the time and effort you invested in this process.\n\nWe wish you the very best of luck in your job search and future endeavors.\n\nSincerely,\n\n[Your Name]\n\n***\n\n*P.S. Just a quick thought, this is a delicate situation, so you don't want to sound like you're offering him a chance to \"re-apply\" if you're not serious about it. It’s kind of the same as a very",
